<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FEFA8728FEC6F42A" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEFA8728FEC6F42A" blockId="29.[241,1224,2908,3187]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
<typeStatus id="54F98877860F6B29FEFA8728FEE1F418" box="[290,379,2908,2947]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Type</typeStatus>
species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FDFF8728FBF5F418" authority="Yoo, 1988: 244" authorityName="Yoo" authorityPageNumber="244" authorityYear="1988" box="[551,1135,2908,2947]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Aclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turgida">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FDFF8728FCD8F418" box="[551,834,2908,2947]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Aclisina turgida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B24860F6B29FC8F8728FBF5F418" author="Yoo, E. K." box="[855,1135,2908,2947]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" pagination="233 - 264" refId="ref27552" refString="Yoo, E. K., 1988. Early Carboniferous Mollusca from Gundy, Upper Hunter, New South Wales. Records of the Australian Museum 40 (4): 233 - 264." type="journal article" year="1988">Yoo, 1988: 244</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, figs 80-81.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FEF887C9FC73F3DB" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEF887C9FC73F3DB" blockId="29.[241,1224,2908,3187]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Definition. Shell minute, with tall-spired convex whorls; protoconch smooth, deviated; teleoconch covered by numerous spiral threads; anomphalous.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FEF98038FBDBF3E8" box="[289,1089,3148,3187]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEF98038FBDBF3E8" blockId="29.[241,1224,2908,3187]" box="[289,1089,3148,3187]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Geological age. Middle to late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FA9D8DECF997FE76" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FA9D8DECF997FE76" blockId="29.[1300,2287,408,913]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
Etymology. Derived from Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29F84C8DECF7BAFE24" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1881" box="[1940,2080,408,447]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Aclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29F84C8DECF7BAFE24" box="[1940,2080,408,447]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Aclisina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a genus of similar shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FA9E8D8DF910FC9D" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FA9E8D8DF910FC9D" blockId="29.[1300,2287,408,913]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
Remarks. The species 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29F8F58D8DF837FDB9" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1988" box="[1837,1965,505,546]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Aclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turgida">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29F8F58D8DF837FDB9" box="[1837,1965,505,546]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">turgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FA138E5CF9CDFDD5" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1881" box="[1483,1623,552,590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Aclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FA138E5CF9CDFDD5" box="[1483,1623,552,590]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Aclisina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Y00, 1988). A further examination of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FA848E22F9B4FDE6" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1988" box="[1372,1582,598,637]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Aclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turgida">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FA848E22F9B4FDE6" box="[1372,1582,598,637]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">A. turgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates that it has a deviated protoconch. No selenizone or notch exists. The species 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FACC8EC6FA78FD43" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1988" box="[1300,1506,690,728]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Aclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turgida">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FACC8EC6FA78FD43" box="[1300,1506,690,728]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">A. turgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29F7C88EC6F732FD43" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1881" box="[2064,2216,690,728]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Aclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29F7C88EC6F732FD43" box="[2064,2216,690,728]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Aclisina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FACD8E94F983FC9D" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1301,1561,736,774]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Pseudoaclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="n.gen.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FACD8E94F983FC9D" box="[1301,1561,736,774]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Pseudoaclisina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860F6B29F9FD8E94F910FC9D" box="[1573,1674,736,774]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" rank="genus">n.gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FA9D8F7AF801FC0A" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="synonymic_list">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FA9D8F7AF801FC0A" blockId="29.[1300,2287,408,913]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
Australian Carboniferous species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29F8308F7AF98AFCF8" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Pseudoaclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="microspirulata" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29F8308F7AF98AFCF8" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Pseudoaclisina microspirulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860F6B29F9EA8F48F919FCF8" box="[1586,1667,828,867]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from 'Marohn'; 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29F83F8F48F995FC0A" authority="(Yoo)" baseAuthorityName="Yoo" baseAuthorityYear="1988" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Pseudoaclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turgida">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29F83F8F48FA0AFC0A" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Pseudoaclisina turgida</emphasis>
(Yoo)
</taxonomicName>
, 1988 from 'Marohn'.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
